==Korean==
===Adjective===
'''고프다''' (''gopeuda'')
#(''for stomach'') To be [[hungry]], [[empty]], [[starved]]

====Alternative spellings====
*[[골프다]] (''golpeuda'')  (''obsolete'') cf. '''[[golf]]''', '''[[gulf]]'''

====Synonyms====
*[[곯다]] (''golhda'') To [[starve]], go [[hungry]], be [[hungry]]
*[[굶다]] (''gulmda'') To [[starve]], go [[hungry]], be [[hungry]]
*[[굶주리다]] (''gulmjurida'') To [[starve]], go [[hungry]], be [[hungry]]
*[[주리다]] (''jurida'') To [[starve]], go [[hungry]],  be [[hungry]]

====Antonyms====
*배[[부르다]] (''bae-bureuda'') (''adjective: for stomach'') To be [[full]]; (''verb: for belly'') to [[bulge]], [[inflate]]  

====Derived terms====
*[[배]]고프다 (''bae-'') To be [[hungry]], [[empty]] (''of stomach'') 

====Related terms====
*[[배]] (''bae'') [[belly]]; [[stomach]]; [[bowel]], [[gut]]  
*[[골]] (''gol, gor'') '''[[hole]]''', [[hollow]], [[furrow]], [[alley]], [[gulley]], [[gullet]], [[valley]]
*[[굴]] (''gul, gur'') '''[[hole]]''', [[hollow]], [[burrow]], [[cavity]], [[cave]], [[tunnel]]
*[[굿]] (''gus, gut'') [[hollow]], [[pit]], [[cavity]] cf. '''[[gut]]''' 

====See also====
